sense.def:
Kadar eno stvar damo
into another thing
, jo damo v notranjost druge stvari.

seg.quote: Pour some water into a glass.
He slipped the note into his pocket.

sense.def:
To go into a place or vehicle
pomeni iti v notranjost nekega prostora ali vozila.

seg.quote: He walked into a police station.

sense.def:
Kadar ena stvar pride
into another thing
, vstopi v drugo stvar in postane njen del.

seg.quote: Drugs may get into the milk.

sense.def:
To bump or crash into something
pomeni po nesreči zadeti ali trčiti v kaj.

To get into a piece of clothing
pomeni zlesti v oblačilo ali si ga nadeti.

seg.quote: She changed into her best dress.

sense.def:
To get into a particular state
pomeni priti v določeno stanje.

seg.quote: The Labour Government came into power in 1974.
The assembly was shocked into silence.

sense.def:
Kadar je nekaj
changed into a new form or shape
, se spremeni ali dobi novo obliko.

seg.quote: The bud develops into a flower.
The play was made into a movie.
I tore her letter into eight pieces.

sense.def:
An investigation into a subject or event
je preiskava, ki se ukvarja z določenim predmetom ali dogodkom.

seg.quote: Some MPs demanded a full enquiry into the incident.
